<div id="query" class="corners">
	<div id="query-main">
		<p class="large-text">
			<img src="/419/img/transparent.gif" class="query-icon-language"/>
			Create wordoids that sound
			<select id="quality" name="quality">
				<option value="1">natural</option>
				<option value="2">almost natural</option>
				<option value="3">hardly natural</option>
			</select>
			in
			<span class="nowrap"><input type="checkbox" id="language-english" name="language"/><label for="language-english">English</label></span>,
			<span class="nowrap"><input type="checkbox" id="language-spanish" name="language"/><label for="language-spanish">Spanish</label></span>,
			<span class="nowrap"><input type="checkbox" id="language-french" name="language"/><label for="language-french">French</label></span>,
			<span class="nowrap"><input type="checkbox" id="language-italian" name="language"/><label for="language-italian">Italian</label></span>,
			<span class="nowrap"><input type="checkbox" id="language-german" name="language"/><label for="language-german">German</label></span>.
		</p>
		<p class="query-tip tiny-text hidden">
			<strong>Quality</strong>. Choose one of the <strong>levels</strong> of how natural wordoids should look, sound or feel.
			The higher the level is, the more the wordoids resemble the usual words of the selected languages.
			<br/>
			<strong>Languages</strong>. Choose <strong>one or more</strong> languages from the list.
			By selecting a <strong>single</strong> language, you get wordoids constructed according to the rules of that language.
			And when you select <strong>two or more</strong> of the languages, wordoids become more sophisticated
			by blending the tastes of these languages.
		</p>
		<p class="large-text">
			<img src="/419/img/transparent.gif" class="query-icon-pattern"/>
			Put <input type="text" id="fragment" maxlength="10"/>
			<select id="position" name="position">
				<option value="1">somewhere inside</option>
				<option value="2">in the beginning of</option>
				<option value="3">in the end of</option>
			</select>
			the wordoids (optional).
		</p>
		<p class="query-tip tiny-text hidden">
			<strong>Pattern</strong>. You may want the wordoids to <strong>begin with</strong>, <strong>end with</strong> or
			<strong>contain</strong> a short fragment. The fragment should consist of the letters <strong>a-z</strong>,
			and may be <strong>at most 10</strong> letters long. Or leave the fragment empty, and the wordoids will be completely random.
		</p>
		<p class="large-text">
			<img src="/419/img/transparent.gif" class="query-icon-length"/>
			Set the wordoid length limit to
			<select id="max-length" name="max-length">
				<option value="5">5</option>
				<option value="6">6</option>
				<option value="7">7</option>
				<option value="8">8</option>
				<option value="9">9</option>
				<option value="10">10</option>
				<option value="11">11</option>
				<option value="12">12</option>
				<option value="13">13</option>
				<option value="14">14</option>
				<option value="15">15</option>
			</select>
			letters.
		</p>
		<p class="query-tip tiny-text hidden">
			<strong>Length</strong>. You may also set the <strong>maximum length</strong> of the wordoids.
			Shorter wordoids tend to look better than longer ones.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div id="query-extra" class="hidden">
		<p class="large-text">
			<img src="/419/img/transparent.gif" class="query-icon-domain"/>
			<select id="domain-availability" name="domain-availability">
				<option value="0">Don't hide</option>
				<option value="1">Hide</option>
			</select>
			wordoids with both <i>.com</i> and <i>.net</i> domains unavailable.
		</p>
		<p class="query-tip tiny-text hidden">
			<strong>Domains</strong>. Choose whether to show or hide wordoids with both <strong>.com</strong> and <strong>.net</strong> domains unavailable.
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div id="query-footer">
